Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro, Molinos Rio de la Plata, YPF Fall

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-04-07T18:35:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/argentine-stocks-banco-macro-molinos-rio-de-la-plata-ypf-fall.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 2 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 1.4 percent to 3,455.77.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)   declined 2.5 percent to 17.75
pesos, the most in three weeks. The price of local sovereign
bonds decreased, signaling lower value for banks’ fixed income
holdings.  Molinos Rio de la Plata (MOLI)  SA retreated 5.2 percent
to 35.40 pesos, and earlier fell 9.5 percent, the most since
April 2009. The Argentine soy processor was removed from the tax
agency’s exporters’ registry yesterday on federal charges it
evaded taxes. Belonging to the registry grants companies tax
breaks on domestic sales and simplifies access to permits,
allowing them to transport products to mills and ports. In a
filing yesterday with the Argentine securities exchange, Molinos
said it would “defend” itself, without giving further details.  YPF SA (YPFD)  , a unit of Spanish oil company Repsol YPF
SA, lost 0.4 percent to 194.75 pesos. A union protest at
 Argentina ’s Refinor SA, a refinery that belongs to YPF and
Petroleo Brasileiro SA, cut natural gas imports from  Bolivia ,
threatening to reduce supplies to industrial users, newspaper El
Cronista said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
